sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J61212
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transposon bearing chloramphenicol resistance on a suicide plasmid bearing spectinomycin resistance. The parts are not actually colinear, as in a normal composite assembly. The coding strand changes at the || indicated in the name.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Josh Kittleson

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J61211
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transposable piece of a transposon bearing suicide plasmid, containing chloramphenicol resistance, an origin of replication for decoding, and a selectable gentimicin marker that only activates when the transposon lands in a transcribed region.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Josh Kittleson

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J61202
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Construction intermediate for a transposon selectable for insertion into a transcribed region.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Josh Kittleson

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J61210
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Intermediate for a transposon with a chloramphenicol resistance marker and a replication origin inside of the transposed region.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Josh Kittleson

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J61209
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Intermediate for construction of a transposon with a plasmid bearing a spectinomycin resistance marker.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Josh Kittleson

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_R0085
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The T7 promoter should only produce PoPS when the T7 polymerase is also being expressed.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Barry Canton

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: FRT
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Site for recombination by flp recombinase. Genes flanked by FRT sites (oriented in the same direction) in the genome can be excised with the introduction of flp recombinase-expressing helper plasmid pCP20. Note that the original FRT sequence contained an XbaI site that has been removed with a point mutation for compatibility with standard assembly. See Datsenko and Wanner for details of its use in markerless knockouts and knockins.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: John Anderson
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance:
Extend ca1010F/R (73 bp, EcoRI/SpeI)
Sub into pSB1A2-I13522 (EcoRI/SpeI)
Product is pSB1A2-Bca1010
---- ca1010F Forward (universal biobrick) EcoRI for FRT
GGACTgaattcgcggccgcttctagag
ca1010R Reverse SpeI oligo for FRT
cctatactagtagaagttcctattctctaAaaagtataggaacttcctctagaagcggccgcg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: CmR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Chloramphenicol resistance gene including its native promoter and ribosome binding site. Confers resistance to 25 ug/mL chloramphenicol.
{pSB1A2-Bca1016}
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: John Anderson
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance:
PCR ca1016F/R on pKD3 (934 bp, EcoRI/SpeI)
Sub into pSB1A2-I13522 (EcoRI/SpeI)
Products are Bca1015 and Bca1016
---- ca1016F Forward EcoRI to biobrick CAT of pKD3
gacttgaattcgcggccgcttctagaggaataggaacttcatttaaatg
ca1016R Reverse SpeI to biobrick CAT of pKD3
ccgctactagtggcgcgcctacctgtgacgg

ca1011R Reverse biobricking of R6K
ccgctactagtaGCAGTTCAACCTGTTGATAG

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: TnP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Tn5 transposase-expressing cassette from pRL. Cassette includes a complete promoter/rbs/orf cassette. The promoter is Ptet, but not derived from r0040. There are PstI and NotI sites in this part, so care must be taken when doing assembly not to use those sites.
pSB1A2-Bca1014
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: John Anderson
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance:
PCR ca1014F/R on pRL27 (1763 bp, EcoRI/SpeI)
Sub into pSB1A2-I13521 (EcoRI/SpeI)
Product is Bca1014 *internal PstI and NotI sites
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: There are PstI and NotI sites in this part, so care must be taken when doing assembly not to use those sites.
